<br>
Rebreathers: 1600 plat each. Almost always have 2 on me. These boys are giant sized and weigh 10 each.<br>
<br>
Aqualungs: 300 plat each. Sell back to vendors for about 200. Makes a great insta-cast junk buff gizmo. 50 charges of Breath of the Dead, usuable from inventory. A nice item to have until you can get your hands on a better insta-cast junk buff item. They weigh 10, are giant sized.  I don't have these in stock.  So give me some advance warnin' if'n you want 'em.<br>
<br>
GVD (Gnomish Vanishing Device): Self only Invis. 5 charges. Rechargable. Anyone can recharge it by using a Deluxe Toolbox (10 slot, holds giant sized items, weighs 3.5) and a class 5 mana battery. Both are sold by the Iceclad gnomes. I can make these... but success rate is low (made 2 out of 30 so far). For that reason, the only way I'm currently making them is a You supply the parts basis. Each attempt requires a Diamond, a Class 5 mana battery, and a Haze Panther Eye. The rest of the parts I'll supply, free of cost. You'll be gambling. You keep however many I make out of what you bring me, no payment to me. But you are running the risk that I'll fail every attempt. It'll stay this way until such time that I can reliably make 'em.  Then this limited time offer ends<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Clockwork Watchman:<br>
Gnome Cleric/Warrior only. All items have 10 charges. Rechargable by anyone by combining the item and a class 5 mana battery in a deluxe toolbox (10 slot, holds giant sized items, weighs 3.5). Both toolbox and batteries are sold by the gnomes in Iceclad. Items must be worn to be used. I typically won't have any in stock and it can take a while to fulfill an order as I need to farm the pieces. To speed up delivery, you can always farm the pieces yourself. All dropped pieces are found in Wakening Lands. Prices for pieces vary based upon the difficulty/time required to farm parts.<br>
<br>
These 3 are relatively easy for me to farm the parts for:<br>
Clockwork Watchman Helm: Self only See Invis. Get the high end helm look for your low level gnome These require Sifaye Dust from Sifaye.<br>
<br>
Clockwork Watchman Vambraces: Cog Boost, a 40% spell haste with 18 minute duration. That's right, spell haste so it stacks with perma haste items. No gnome warrior should be without these. These require Holgresh Fur from Holgresh.<br>
<br>
Clockwork Watchman Greaves: Grease Injection, a 40% movement rate increase (same speed as j-boots), 18 minute duration. 13 AC. These require Holgresh Wings from Holgresh.<br>
<br>
And these aren't... if you want 'em, best help me farm the parts for 'em:<br>
Clockwork Watchman Gloves: Steam Injection, a +30 str buff that lasts an hour, if I recall right. Supposedly stacks with other strength buffs. Haven't made any yet, so haven't tested that personally. These require Block of Living Granite from Geonids.<br>
<br>
Clockwork Watchman Bracers: Summon Wrench, summons a 6/26 no rent, no drop magical &quot;wrench&quot; that looks like a hammer. These require globs of tar from the Tar Goos.<br>
<br>
Clockwork Watchman Boots: Mana Infusion, a +30 dex buff that lasts an hour, supposedly stacks with other dex buffs. Haven't made any yet, so haven't tested it personally. These require Faun Hooves from Fauns.<br>
<br>
And this one, well..., it's a you provide parts type deal. <br>
Clockwork Watchman Breastplate: Invisibility Cloak. Self only invis. This requires a GVD (Gnomish Vanishing Device). For details on that, well, see it's category. I don't expect to be making these until I get quite a bit higher skill.<br>
<br>
Non-Clockwork:<br>
I don't bother with most of the lower level stuff. Although I guess I could make up a batch of cams or spyglasses if someone were to order a large (10+) quantity.<br>
<br>
Axterix En'Obelix<br>
Master Tinkerer (178 skill) of Zebuxurok<br>
